WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.003
(FLY BUZZES)

00:04.880 --> 00:06.882
(CHAINS CLINKING)

00:21.897 --> 00:23.899
(WALKERS GROWLING)

00:31.323 --> 00:32.491
(GUNSHOT)

00:34.368 --> 00:36.745
(WALKERS GROWLING)

00:36.828 --> 00:38.163
Shit.

01:03.564 --> 01:05.566
(GRUNTING)

01:07.276 --> 01:10.863
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

01:10.946 --> 01:14.199
(SCREAMING)

01:24.042 --> 01:28.881
WOMAN: Oh, no, no, no, no!

01:28.964 --> 01:30.966
(SCREAMING)

01:32.634 --> 01:34.636
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:22.809 --> 02:25.354
You couldn't have done that
five hours ago?

02:25.437 --> 02:28.524
Why would I do that?

02:28.607 --> 02:30.609
(GRUNTING)

02:36.907 --> 02:39.243
Come on.
Family's inland.

02:39.326 --> 02:41.245
And the munitions?

02:41.328 --> 02:43.747
Everything's inland.

03:04.393 --> 03:05.394
MICHONNE: I need to get back.

03:05.477 --> 03:07.145
We headed in?

03:07.229 --> 03:09.982
Well, I can't show up
empty-handed.

03:10.065 --> 03:11.650
Wife wouldn't like that.

03:11.733 --> 03:13.068
Oh, my God.

03:13.151 --> 03:14.903
VIRGIL: This garden's her baby.

03:14.987 --> 03:17.781
Got herbs and teas
for everything,

03:17.865 --> 03:20.909
pain, nerves, sleep.

03:20.993 --> 03:22.578
How 'bout focus and speed?

03:22.661 --> 03:26.039
Well, those Whisper folk
really got you percolatin', huh?

03:26.123 --> 03:27.791
There's a lot of lives at stake.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.878
Where are these munition depots
you spoke of?

03:30.961 --> 03:32.880
Is this one of them?

03:32.963 --> 03:35.799
VIRGIL: Nah, that's just
an old lab,

03:35.883 --> 03:37.217
some structural damage.

03:37.301 --> 03:39.720
Wild animals
get in there sometimes.

03:39.803 --> 03:42.181
Best to stay away.

03:42.264 --> 03:43.432
(GRUNTS)

04:01.867 --> 04:02.993
(GRUNTS)

04:07.289 --> 04:10.000
MICHONNE: My kids
would run riot in here.

04:14.296 --> 04:16.965
My boy seems to think
maybe the sailors must've left

04:17.049 --> 04:21.929
a buried treasure
in the grain silos.

04:22.012 --> 04:24.431
I can barely get him
not to claw his way up the thing

04:24.515 --> 04:26.975
and jump inside.

04:30.020 --> 04:31.188
Kid's 5.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.648
(CHUCKLES)

04:34.483 --> 04:36.109
He's just like his mom.

04:40.113 --> 04:41.448
Once they decide
to do somethin',

04:41.532 --> 04:45.035
ain't a damn thing you can do
to stop 'em.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.746
I remember one time I...

04:47.829 --> 04:49.790
Stop the bullshit.

04:49.873 --> 04:52.543
Now, where the hell
is your family?

04:55.754 --> 04:57.965
VIRGIL: When I said I had to
come home to my family,

04:59.341 --> 05:00.634
I meant it.

05:02.970 --> 05:06.306
I promised her
when we got married.

05:06.390 --> 05:08.100
Flowers every day.

05:08.183 --> 05:10.310
How are you gonna wait till now
to tell me this?

05:12.396 --> 05:14.857
(SCOFFS)

05:14.940 --> 05:16.441
Those words don't come easy.

05:16.525 --> 05:18.151
I don't like
to bring people here.

05:19.987 --> 05:21.363
Don't trust 'em.

05:21.446 --> 05:22.906
I was scared.

05:22.990 --> 05:26.159
MICHONNE: Are there
any weapons here at all?

05:26.243 --> 05:27.911
I promised
I would help you check,

05:27.995 --> 05:29.663
and I will, but...

05:29.746 --> 05:32.040
-Ugh, I'm gonna find 'em myself.
-The island's not clear.

05:32.124 --> 05:34.710
No shit it's not clear!

05:34.793 --> 05:38.005
VIRGIL: It was until the others came.

05:38.088 --> 05:39.590
They brought violence.

05:42.092 --> 05:43.969
The sickness came with it.

05:44.052 --> 05:45.304
Killed my family.

05:45.387 --> 05:47.556
We never had a lotta Rippers.

05:47.639 --> 05:50.017
So I never really got good at...

05:50.100 --> 05:54.980
doing (SIGHS) what it is you do.

05:55.063 --> 05:56.982
You're good with a sword.

05:57.065 --> 05:58.734
What are you askin' me?

06:01.862 --> 06:03.488
My family's still in there.

06:05.866 --> 06:07.951
My wife.

06:08.035 --> 06:10.329
My babies.

06:10.412 --> 06:13.040
That's why I asked you to come.

06:13.123 --> 06:15.167
Needed you to come.

06:18.170 --> 06:20.797
(GROWLING)

06:31.600 --> 06:34.019
-(METAL CLINKS)
-(GROWLING)

06:36.146 --> 06:39.024
(BANGING ON DOOR)

06:42.277 --> 06:43.987
(FLESH TEARS, GROWLING STOPS)

06:44.071 --> 06:45.072
(THUD)

06:47.324 --> 06:50.035
(GROWLING IN DISTANCE)

07:23.902 --> 07:25.863
(GROWLING STOPS)

07:42.045 --> 07:44.047
(GROWLING IN DISTANCE)

08:12.451 --> 08:13.911
(GRUNTS)

08:13.994 --> 08:16.788
(METAL CLANGING)

08:18.790 --> 08:21.168
Shit. Sorry.

08:21.251 --> 08:23.253
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

08:28.550 --> 08:29.885
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

08:29.968 --> 08:31.303
VIRGIL: What do we do?

08:36.683 --> 08:39.019
Follow me. Stay close.

08:39.102 --> 08:40.771
(GRUNTS)

08:46.026 --> 08:47.361
(GRUNTING)

08:59.831 --> 09:02.000
Get behind that now.

09:02.084 --> 09:04.920
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

09:20.978 --> 09:22.646
(GROWLING STOPS)

09:26.483 --> 09:27.943
Thank you.

09:39.371 --> 09:41.832
(WALKERS GROWLING)

10:11.737 --> 10:13.739
(WALKERS GROWLING)

11:09.419 --> 11:11.922
VIRGIL: I wanted to give them
somethin' they loved

11:12.005 --> 11:13.549
to take with 'em.

11:16.176 --> 11:18.720
And Jasmine loved that book.

11:18.804 --> 11:20.889
Look, I know that this is hard,
and I am sorry,

11:20.973 --> 11:22.891
but I have got to get back.

11:22.975 --> 11:26.395
My wife,
whenever I had a hard time,

11:26.478 --> 11:29.439
she'd talk me through it.

11:29.523 --> 11:31.316
Without her,
I don't know who I am.

11:31.400 --> 11:34.111
It's not too late
to find out. Look...

11:34.194 --> 11:35.571
I wanted to ask you...

11:41.535 --> 11:43.453
It's been a long time

11:43.537 --> 11:45.539
since I had a reason
to say thank you to someone.

11:45.622 --> 11:46.957
Don't thank me.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.333
Just show me
what I came here for,

11:48.417 --> 11:49.418
and I'll go.

11:49.501 --> 11:51.670
No, it's gettin' late.

11:51.753 --> 11:53.172
Tide's low.

11:53.255 --> 11:54.882
Oh, God.

11:54.965 --> 11:57.843
VIRGIL: I'm not sure the boat'll
make it through the channel.

11:57.926 --> 11:59.469
Might wanna stay here tonight
and not risk it.

11:59.553 --> 12:03.265
Virgil, I need you to hold up
your end of the bargain.

12:03.348 --> 12:04.349
VIRGIL: Yeah. But...

12:04.433 --> 12:07.561
(GRUNTS)

12:07.644 --> 12:09.021
It's gettin' dark,

12:09.104 --> 12:11.773
and some of the buildings
aren't safe.

12:11.857 --> 12:14.443
Could we do this in the morning?

12:14.526 --> 12:17.863
We can do it first thing.

12:28.957 --> 12:30.959
(WALKIE-TALKIE CLICKS, STATIC)

12:35.380 --> 12:37.174
(WALKIE-TALKIE TURNS OFF,
THUDS)

12:40.844 --> 12:42.846
-(OWL HOOTING)
-(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

12:50.562 --> 12:53.148
(DOOR CLANKS, CREAKS)

13:00.531 --> 13:03.492
(DOOR CREAKS, CLOSES)

13:13.544 --> 13:15.420
(DOOR CLANKS)

13:28.475 --> 13:29.893
(SIGHS)

13:34.273 --> 13:36.692
MAN: (WHISPERING)
Stay still. Everyone quiet.

14:04.636 --> 14:06.513
MAN: Is it him?

14:06.597 --> 14:08.307
WOMAN: I don't know.

14:08.390 --> 14:10.392
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

14:14.521 --> 14:17.816
-MAN: What is that?
-WOMAN: I don't know. Quiet.

14:17.900 --> 14:21.069
-Stop moving.
-MAN: It might not be him.

14:21.153 --> 14:23.322
Shh.

14:23.405 --> 14:25.115
-No, I don't know.
-Be calm.

14:25.199 --> 14:28.744
WOMAN: Stop moving.

14:28.827 --> 14:31.371
(VIRGIL SIGHS)

14:34.458 --> 14:35.667
Virgil!

14:35.751 --> 14:37.878
VIRGIL: Why couldn't you
just wait until morning?

14:37.961 --> 14:39.046
I told you it wasn't safe.

14:39.129 --> 14:40.672
Virgil, open the damn door.

14:40.756 --> 14:44.259
I trusted you, and you ruined it.

14:44.343 --> 14:46.094
Open the damn door, Virgil!

14:46.178 --> 14:47.179
(BANGING ON DOOR)

14:47.262 --> 14:51.141
Virgil! Virgil!

14:51.225 --> 14:53.018
Virgil!

14:56.480 --> 14:58.482
(GRUNTING)

15:02.736 --> 15:05.614
(PANTING)

15:05.697 --> 15:07.699
(WATER DRIPPING)

15:18.460 --> 15:19.837
(GASPS)

15:19.920 --> 15:21.922
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

15:25.259 --> 15:27.845
Oh, shit!

15:27.928 --> 15:31.098
(PANTING)

15:31.181 --> 15:33.183
(GRUNTING)

15:37.563 --> 15:40.858
(BANGING ON DOOR)

15:40.941 --> 15:43.068
Damn it.

15:43.151 --> 15:44.987
MAN: Calm down.

15:47.531 --> 15:48.532
MICHONNE: Hello?

15:48.615 --> 15:50.784
WOMAN: We've been trying
to talk to you.

15:50.868 --> 15:52.786
How long have I been in here?

15:53.996 --> 15:55.205
A day maybe?

15:55.289 --> 15:57.833
(SIGHS) A day?

15:57.916 --> 15:59.001
MICHONNE: Why didn't you answer me

15:59.084 --> 16:00.794
when I called out to you
the first time?

16:00.878 --> 16:02.588
He blows up at us sometimes.

16:02.671 --> 16:04.256
Gets in one of his moods.

16:04.339 --> 16:06.758
When he's angry like that,
it's best to be quiet.

16:06.842 --> 16:08.260
MICHONNE: You guys know
this building, right?

16:08.343 --> 16:09.845
What's the layout?

16:09.928 --> 16:11.680
WOMAN:
Don't bother trying to escape.

16:11.763 --> 16:13.432
MAN: Whole place
is booby-trapped.

16:13.515 --> 16:15.601
MICHONNE: What's his routine?
How often does he come around?

16:15.684 --> 16:16.852
As little as possible.

16:16.935 --> 16:19.563
He doesn't like to see us.

16:19.646 --> 16:21.648
(SIGHS)

16:23.400 --> 16:25.611
Celeste and I were researchers
with Virgil.

16:25.694 --> 16:27.571
We wrote the papers.

16:27.654 --> 16:30.115
-Yeah, and I swept the floors.
-She assisted us.

16:30.199 --> 16:32.701
So you had a life here.
You knew each other.

16:32.784 --> 16:36.205
Yeah, we were friends with Virgil.

16:36.288 --> 16:39.291
Tell me what went wrong.

16:39.374 --> 16:41.460
LUCY: Stragglers used to come
by boat,

16:41.543 --> 16:44.254
stumble on us,
and we took 'em in.

16:44.338 --> 16:45.422
We took 'em all in.

16:45.506 --> 16:47.216
JEREMIAH:
One night, it got really bad.

16:47.299 --> 16:48.509
Food supplies
were gettin' low,

16:48.592 --> 16:52.012
and a fight broke out
over the rations and...

16:52.095 --> 16:55.098
LUCY: And somebody pulled
a knife, and this newbie died.

16:55.182 --> 16:57.851
JEREMIAH:
Virgil was late gettin' there,

16:57.935 --> 16:59.394
panicked.

16:59.478 --> 17:01.396
Said we need
to lock all the doors.

17:01.480 --> 17:04.358
LUCY:
He didn't know.

17:04.441 --> 17:07.069
Virgil didn't know.

17:07.152 --> 17:09.780
Know what?

17:09.863 --> 17:12.241
His wife and kids were inside.

17:15.410 --> 17:16.828
(SIGHS)

17:22.459 --> 17:23.669
He snapped.

17:23.752 --> 17:26.171
JEREMIAH:
He was never the same.

17:26.255 --> 17:30.050
LUCY:
We've been in here ever since.

17:30.133 --> 17:31.218
JEREMIAH: You okay?

17:31.301 --> 17:32.636
I will be.

17:34.596 --> 17:36.390
I'm not stayin' here long.

17:36.473 --> 17:39.059
LUCY: You need some rest.
Eat something.

17:39.142 --> 17:41.144
The food should be okay.

17:41.228 --> 17:43.355
Save your strength.

17:43.438 --> 17:45.440
You can't kill him
if you don't have your strength.

17:49.111 --> 17:50.988
CELESTE: You haven't
told us your name.

17:54.157 --> 17:56.785
It's Michonne.

17:56.869 --> 17:57.953
(CLANK)

17:58.036 --> 18:00.038
(PANTING)

18:07.004 --> 18:08.213
I'm glad you ate.

18:08.297 --> 18:10.716
Open the damn door!

18:10.799 --> 18:11.967
VIRGIL:
I can't do that.

18:12.050 --> 18:13.302
Why the hell not?

18:13.385 --> 18:14.845
Because you'll kill me.

18:14.928 --> 18:16.221
I know you will.

18:16.305 --> 18:19.683
Well, we reap what we sow,
asshole.

18:20.851 --> 18:23.187
(ECHOING)
I don't wanna fight.

18:24.563 --> 18:27.191
I want you to understand.

18:33.780 --> 18:36.200
(GRUNTING, WHIMPERING)

18:39.870 --> 18:42.497
The island has a gift.

18:44.082 --> 18:48.003
It can help you
the way it helped me.

18:50.672 --> 18:51.757
(ECHOING) Aah!

18:51.840 --> 18:53.842
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

18:56.678 --> 18:58.222
(GRUNTS)

19:06.480 --> 19:08.482
What the hell did you do?

19:13.904 --> 19:15.906
(WATER DRIPPING ECHOES)

19:25.499 --> 19:27.501
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

19:38.512 --> 19:39.847
What did you... What did you...

19:39.930 --> 19:42.349
(ECHOING) Jimsonweed.

19:42.432 --> 19:44.810
Makes a nice tea.

19:44.893 --> 19:46.436
Calming.

19:46.520 --> 19:48.480
I want you to see.

19:50.107 --> 19:51.859
You don't think I see it,
but I do.

19:51.942 --> 19:55.487
You're in pain, like me.

19:55.571 --> 19:57.865
You need peace, like me.

19:57.948 --> 20:00.617
Like you? No.

20:00.701 --> 20:02.661
I don't drug people
and toss them in cells.

20:02.744 --> 20:04.371
"Toss them in cells"?
Yes, you've said.

20:04.454 --> 20:07.666
We've had that conversation
three times.

20:09.084 --> 20:11.378
I need you to hear me.

20:11.461 --> 20:14.923
I need you to think about
my daughter and my son.

20:15.007 --> 20:16.133
VIRGIL: "Think you about
my daughter and my son."

20:16.216 --> 20:19.344
Yes, I said those words, too,
but no one listened.

20:20.929 --> 20:23.265
Everything I did
was to protect my family.

20:23.348 --> 20:27.102
Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho, I'm sure
they're real proud of you now.

20:27.186 --> 20:28.770
SIDDIQ (ECHOING):
What about my child?

20:28.854 --> 20:30.856
My family?

20:37.613 --> 20:39.114
You're no angel.

20:39.198 --> 20:40.532
(WALKER GROWLS)

20:43.160 --> 20:45.162
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

20:47.331 --> 20:49.541
I'm so cold.

20:49.625 --> 20:51.668
It's cold. It's cold.

20:51.752 --> 20:53.253
SIDDIQ:
So picture the sun.

20:53.337 --> 20:55.339
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

21:00.761 --> 21:04.973
Let the medicine do its work.

21:17.611 --> 21:18.737
Siddiq.

21:23.992 --> 21:26.537
You were supposed to
protect us.

21:27.955 --> 21:29.164
I did my best.

21:29.248 --> 21:31.959
You let me die.

21:32.042 --> 21:36.046
-No!
-And Rick and Carl.

21:37.130 --> 21:38.799
What happens to Coco?

21:38.882 --> 21:40.592
What happens to my family?

21:40.676 --> 21:41.760
(CRYING) You are my family.

21:41.844 --> 21:46.056
Well, this is how it feels
to be your family!

21:50.310 --> 21:51.645
(GROWLS)

21:51.728 --> 21:53.730
Stop! Stop it! Stop!

21:54.898 --> 21:56.900
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

22:04.491 --> 22:07.077
Siddiq?

22:07.160 --> 22:09.162
(CHAINS CLINKING)

22:20.757 --> 22:22.843
VIRGIL'S VOICE:
Stop fighting it.

22:27.973 --> 22:29.558
(ECHOING) She's waiting.

22:32.102 --> 22:34.730
(SIGHS)

22:40.777 --> 22:42.237
(GRUNTS)

22:42.321 --> 22:44.323
(WALKERS GROWLING)

22:47.451 --> 22:49.203
(GRUNTS)

22:55.125 --> 22:58.545
Oh, no, no, no, no!

23:00.214 --> 23:02.257
(SCREAMING)

23:27.950 --> 23:29.034
(SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

23:32.412 --> 23:34.414
(WALKERS GROWLING)

23:41.171 --> 23:42.965
MICHONNE: (ECHOING) Hey!

23:45.968 --> 23:47.594
Help!

23:47.678 --> 23:50.639
Help! Please!

23:50.722 --> 23:52.140
-Help me! Please!
-Come on. Let's go!

23:52.224 --> 23:54.768
(SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

23:54.852 --> 23:56.353
Please!

24:00.440 --> 24:03.151
(WALKER GROWLING)

24:03.235 --> 24:05.070
-(GROWLING STOPS)
-(GRUNTING)

24:08.782 --> 24:13.161
Well, looky what we have here.

24:19.251 --> 24:21.253
(GRUNTING)

24:23.338 --> 24:25.340
Goddamn.

24:25.424 --> 24:27.759
This chick has some cojones.

24:27.843 --> 24:29.553
(NORMAL VOICE)
I don't want any trouble.

24:29.636 --> 24:30.888
Well, then,
you probably shouldn't have

24:30.971 --> 24:32.514
taken a swing at me.

24:32.598 --> 24:35.350
Or I probably
shouldn't have missed.

24:35.434 --> 24:37.769
(CHUCKLES)

24:37.853 --> 24:40.105
(GROANS)

24:40.189 --> 24:41.690
(SIGHS)

24:43.692 --> 24:46.820
You know, I'm not much on
savin' people on the road,

24:46.904 --> 24:50.199
especially those
that try to take my head off,

24:50.282 --> 24:53.952
but I gotta say, I like you

24:54.036 --> 24:58.749
and your big,
ol' massive lady nuts.

24:58.832 --> 25:02.002
Besides, be a waste

25:02.085 --> 25:06.089
to have such a nice sword
and no strength to use it.

25:13.222 --> 25:15.057
(ECHOING) Name's Negan.

25:29.821 --> 25:31.365
(FLESH TEARS)

25:35.619 --> 25:38.539
(GUNSHOTS)

25:51.885 --> 25:53.095
(ALARM BLARING)

25:53.178 --> 25:54.930
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

25:55.013 --> 25:57.015
NEGAN: (WHISTLING)

26:13.991 --> 26:16.076
NEGAN: Eenie...

26:16.159 --> 26:18.704
meenie...

26:18.787 --> 26:21.164
miney...

26:21.248 --> 26:23.250
Nah.

26:23.333 --> 26:25.502
Just kiddin', assholes.

26:25.586 --> 26:29.214
See, I was gonna do
this next part myself,

26:29.298 --> 26:32.801
but, see, my right-hand gal,
(ECHOING) Michonne,

26:32.885 --> 26:35.179
is on a wicked-ass tear
these days,

26:35.262 --> 26:39.141
and who the hell am I
to stand in her way?

26:46.231 --> 26:48.442
(NORMAL VOICE) Mm.

26:53.071 --> 26:56.825
You wish 'em a happy new year
from us, will ya?

27:00.204 --> 27:01.622
(SCOFFS)

27:04.249 --> 27:06.210
You didn't know who they were...

27:06.293 --> 27:08.545
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

27:08.629 --> 27:10.297
...or where they were from.

27:13.008 --> 27:15.886
(ECHOING) You didn't know shit
about them.

27:15.969 --> 27:18.764
But you came
in the dead of night

27:21.350 --> 27:26.230
and slaughtered them anyway
in their sleep.

27:37.449 --> 27:39.910
Like cowards.

27:53.882 --> 27:56.677
Ah.

28:05.769 --> 28:07.396
And you remember...

28:09.481 --> 28:11.733
you did this.

28:11.817 --> 28:13.694
What happens next...

28:16.655 --> 28:18.448
it's your fault.

28:20.659 --> 28:23.161
Welcome to the new world.

28:25.163 --> 28:26.915
Ha!

28:30.544 --> 28:32.921
(GUNFIRE)

28:35.757 --> 28:38.010
(GRUNTING)

28:44.558 --> 28:46.351
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

28:51.231 --> 28:52.774
(GRUNTS)

29:04.494 --> 29:05.704
(GUN COCKS)

29:10.292 --> 29:11.376
(GUNSHOT)

29:11.460 --> 29:13.462
(RETCHING, COUGHING)

29:16.381 --> 29:18.383
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:28.227 --> 29:30.020
(KEYS JINGLE)

29:30.103 --> 29:31.396
VIRGIL:
You feel better?

29:31.480 --> 29:33.482
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:34.983 --> 29:36.610
You will.

29:48.914 --> 29:50.457
Aah!

29:52.626 --> 29:55.504
(BOTH GRUNTING)

30:05.806 --> 30:08.058
(BLADE CLANGS)

30:10.143 --> 30:11.520
-LUCY: Michonne.
-JEREMIAH: Don't leave us.

30:11.603 --> 30:12.688
CELESTE:
Let us out. Please.

30:12.771 --> 30:13.897
JEREMIAH: Michonne.

30:27.619 --> 30:32.124
-(FIRE CRACKLING)
-CELESTE: Oh, shit.

30:32.207 --> 30:34.209
(PANTING)

30:39.089 --> 30:41.091
(GRUNTING)

30:51.435 --> 30:52.936
I was gonna ask you to help me.

30:53.020 --> 30:54.855
I wanted to let them go.

30:54.938 --> 30:56.565
I wanted you to be there
so they wouldn't kill me.

30:56.648 --> 30:58.233
Then you found 'em first,

30:58.317 --> 31:00.235
and I knew
you were gonna kill me, too.

31:00.319 --> 31:01.403
I'm sorry.

31:01.486 --> 31:03.488
You're sorry?
"Sorry" doesn't cut it.

31:03.572 --> 31:05.574
(SCREAMS)

31:06.700 --> 31:09.119
She always told me
the right thing to do,

31:09.203 --> 31:12.497
and then she was gone
and I didn't know what to do.

31:12.581 --> 31:15.709
And I couldn't let you leave,
and I didn't wanna kill you.

31:15.792 --> 31:17.503
Move, Michonne.

31:17.586 --> 31:20.088
You have as much reason
to kill this asshole as we do.

31:20.172 --> 31:21.507
I do.

31:21.590 --> 31:23.592
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

31:43.278 --> 31:46.949
-(SIGHS)
-CELESTE: Do it or move.

31:52.454 --> 31:53.580
Look at him.

31:56.041 --> 31:59.378
He owes you more
than he can ever make right.

32:01.046 --> 32:02.631
Taking his life...

32:05.843 --> 32:08.011
you'll lose more of yourself.

32:09.721 --> 32:11.348
It doesn't settle it.

32:12.349 --> 32:15.686
But your mercy
gives you something.

32:15.769 --> 32:17.396
You get something.

32:17.479 --> 32:20.023
What?

32:20.107 --> 32:21.191
Peace.

32:30.117 --> 32:31.118
(LUCY AND VIRGIL GRUNT)

32:38.250 --> 32:40.043
(MICHONNE SIGHS)

32:44.965 --> 32:46.758
MICHONNE:
There's nothing here.

32:46.842 --> 32:48.177
I checked every building,

32:48.260 --> 32:51.346
even the ones you said
had structural damage.

32:51.430 --> 32:54.016
Not a Goddamn thing anywhere.

32:54.099 --> 32:56.852
I know you don't have
any reason to believe me,

32:58.687 --> 33:00.772
but I never lied to you about the weapons.

33:00.856 --> 33:02.524
You said you'd seen them.

33:02.608 --> 33:05.611
I told you
I could show you the spots.

33:05.694 --> 33:07.654
I got no reason to go in them.

33:07.738 --> 33:09.740
You have got
to do better than that.

33:09.823 --> 33:11.408
VIRGIL:
I'm sorry. I can't.

33:11.491 --> 33:14.286
Sometimes we find
a stray shell,

33:14.369 --> 33:16.705
but never any more than...

33:16.788 --> 33:21.502
I... I find a stray shell.

33:21.585 --> 33:23.003
(CHUCKLES)

33:23.086 --> 33:24.755
I'm not going back empty-handed.

33:24.838 --> 33:25.923
VIRGIL:
Take whatever you want.

33:26.006 --> 33:27.466
Clear my debt with Oceanside.

33:27.549 --> 33:31.345
-(KEYS JINGLE)
-(MICHONNE SIGHS)

33:31.428 --> 33:33.055
You took the risk.

33:33.138 --> 33:34.306
MICHONNE:
Didn't have a choice.

33:36.558 --> 33:38.143
I had to find out.

33:41.897 --> 33:43.941
And there's no tea,
so don't even ask.

33:52.282 --> 33:55.160
What do you see when
you're trippin', anyway?

33:57.496 --> 34:00.666
Lisa with that damn camera
pointed at everyone.

34:01.708 --> 34:03.126
My babies.

34:04.419 --> 34:05.921
(CHUCKLES)

34:07.548 --> 34:10.342
Jasmine sittin' by the fire
with that book,

34:11.677 --> 34:13.428
askin' a million questions

34:13.512 --> 34:15.556
about a world
she'll never know.

34:19.726 --> 34:22.479
Bobby and me lyin'
on the roof of that Annex,

34:22.563 --> 34:24.815
lookin' up at the stars.

34:27.484 --> 34:28.694
Heaven.

34:32.531 --> 34:34.116
I wanted...

34:35.367 --> 34:38.370
hoped that
you would see that, too.

34:43.000 --> 34:44.960
It took my family from me.

34:46.378 --> 34:48.255
I saw hell.

34:49.756 --> 34:51.425
I'm sorry.

34:53.093 --> 34:56.054
Only world I ever wanted
was one they were in.

34:57.181 --> 34:59.558
I don't know how to do this
without them.

34:59.641 --> 35:02.853
You try, like the rest of us.

35:04.605 --> 35:07.941
Now, how 'bout
you try to find my stuff?

35:10.110 --> 35:12.613
(DOOR CREAKS)

36:03.413 --> 36:06.250
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

36:11.630 --> 36:14.091
(GRUNTS)

36:14.174 --> 36:15.717
Where the hell
did you get these?

36:17.427 --> 36:19.096
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

36:30.941 --> 36:32.025
VIRGIL:
It washed up.

36:32.109 --> 36:33.360
(GRUNTS)

36:33.443 --> 36:34.778
It washed up
during the big storm.

36:34.862 --> 36:37.114
I don't know
where the hell it came from.

36:37.197 --> 36:39.616
(GRUNTING) Wait.

36:39.700 --> 36:40.701
No!

36:40.784 --> 36:41.869
Michonne.

36:41.952 --> 36:44.538
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

37:25.662 --> 37:28.373
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

37:33.045 --> 37:36.256
Holy shit.

37:38.050 --> 37:39.426
That's you.

37:41.220 --> 37:42.346
And the kid?

37:50.812 --> 37:52.231
MICHONNE: You knew.

37:55.526 --> 37:57.903
You came to find us
at Oceanside.

37:57.986 --> 37:59.696
VIRGIL:
No. (SCOFFS)

37:59.780 --> 38:00.781
What?

38:00.864 --> 38:03.242
Uh, uh, why would I do that?

38:03.325 --> 38:04.493
Because of this.

38:04.576 --> 38:06.453
I have never seen that before
in my life.

38:06.537 --> 38:07.538
I swear.

38:07.621 --> 38:09.581
But why are his things here?
What was he doing here?

38:09.665 --> 38:11.124
How the hell would I know?

38:11.208 --> 38:13.293
You knew that this boat was here
this whole time.

38:13.377 --> 38:14.545
VIRGIL:
The world ended.

38:14.628 --> 38:15.796
Boats wash up.

38:15.879 --> 38:17.464
What do you want me to say?

38:17.548 --> 38:18.757
(GRUNTS)

38:18.841 --> 38:20.676
You knew
that there were no munitions.

38:20.759 --> 38:22.094
Were you setting up a trap
for us?

38:22.177 --> 38:23.595
Did you lay a trap for him?

38:23.679 --> 38:24.847
What did you do?

38:24.930 --> 38:26.265
What did you do to him?

38:26.348 --> 38:28.267
(BREATHING RAPIDLY)

38:28.350 --> 38:32.187
Who are you talking about?

38:50.289 --> 38:51.623
(SNIFFLES)

39:01.758 --> 39:05.179
VIRGIL: I don't know what it is
you think I have

39:07.472 --> 39:09.558
or who
you're looking for, but...

39:13.520 --> 39:16.398
maybe it wasn't an accident
that we met.

39:19.276 --> 39:20.360
If the others will help me,

39:20.444 --> 39:22.905
I think we can mod the engine
and get it workin' again.

39:26.617 --> 39:28.619
If this person was on this boat,

39:30.370 --> 39:32.331
then maybe you can
find them again.

39:37.336 --> 39:39.338
(MICHONNE SOBBING)

39:40.547 --> 39:43.550
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

40:14.998 --> 40:16.667
Gonna take some time.

40:16.750 --> 40:18.794
We're out of time.

40:18.877 --> 40:20.629
They're willing to let you come.

40:20.712 --> 40:22.506
They say that?

40:22.589 --> 40:24.383
MICHONNE:
There's only one boat left.

40:24.466 --> 40:26.009
You leave now
or you don't leave.

40:27.010 --> 40:28.595
After everything,

40:29.721 --> 40:32.099
I can't believe
they would do that.

40:32.182 --> 40:35.686
MICHONNE: Sometimes the most
injured are the most forgiving.

40:35.769 --> 40:39.815
They're good people, Virgil,
and they're trying,

40:41.066 --> 40:44.278
giving you a chance,
a way off of this island.

40:47.197 --> 40:51.368
I promised her flowers
every day.

40:52.661 --> 40:53.996
(SIGHS)

41:31.867 --> 41:35.120
(MICHONNE CRYING)

41:44.046 --> 41:46.215
(SNIFFLES)

41:57.851 --> 41:59.061
Shoto.

42:01.146 --> 42:02.189
Shoto, are you there?

42:02.272 --> 42:03.565
It's Daito.

42:06.193 --> 42:07.277
Shoto?

42:08.612 --> 42:10.197
Are you out there?
Anyone?

42:15.619 --> 42:17.079
JUDITH:
<i>I'm here, Daito.</i>

42:21.333 --> 42:22.835
I've been trying you.

42:22.918 --> 42:24.169
(INHALES SHARPLY)

42:24.253 --> 42:25.546
I'm sorry.

42:25.629 --> 42:26.755
I'm here now.

42:26.839 --> 42:28.549
Are you still with Virgil?

42:28.632 --> 42:31.385
<i>MICHONNE: No, but I found</i>
<i>three people on the island,</i>

42:31.468 --> 42:33.554
and I'm helping them
get back home.

42:34.847 --> 42:38.267
I've missed you
and your brother so much.

42:38.350 --> 42:39.685
Mama.

42:40.978 --> 42:41.979
JUDITH: <i>No, no.</i>

42:42.062 --> 42:43.939
Call signs for safety.

42:44.022 --> 42:45.232
Daito.

42:45.315 --> 42:47.109
You're Daito.

42:47.192 --> 42:49.236
Hey, baby.

42:49.319 --> 42:50.529
And who are you?

42:50.612 --> 42:52.322
RJ:
<i>I'm Little Brave Man.</i>

42:52.406 --> 42:53.699
Oh.

42:56.994 --> 42:59.037
I love "Little Brave Man."

42:59.121 --> 43:00.706
JUDITH:
<i>He picked it all by himself.</i>

43:02.124 --> 43:05.252
How long have you been with
your sister, Little Brave Man?

43:05.335 --> 43:08.005
Tia Rosita brought me.

43:11.550 --> 43:12.634
Judith...

43:15.304 --> 43:18.140
<i>how are Tia Rosita</i>
<i>and Coco doing?</i>

43:18.223 --> 43:20.517
Okay, I guess.

43:20.601 --> 43:21.727
Better.

43:21.810 --> 43:23.312
How's home?

43:23.395 --> 43:24.688
Anything with the Whisperers?

43:29.443 --> 43:30.444
We got 'em, Mom.

43:32.571 --> 43:33.947
<i>We got most of the horde.</i>

43:35.741 --> 43:36.992
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

43:38.577 --> 43:40.412
Alpha can't hurt us anymore.

43:40.495 --> 43:42.372
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

43:44.958 --> 43:46.752
JUDITH:
<i>You're doing it again.</i>

43:46.835 --> 43:49.171
<i>You always make that sound</i>
<i>when you're worried.</i>

43:49.254 --> 43:50.255
Do not.

43:50.339 --> 43:51.381
Do, too.

43:52.466 --> 43:54.843
(SNIFFLES)

43:54.927 --> 43:56.512
Um...

43:58.263 --> 43:59.515
I found something.

44:01.350 --> 44:03.060
<i>Not what I was looking for</i>
<i>on the island,</i>

44:03.143 --> 44:05.729
<i>but something else,</i>
<i>something that...</i>

44:06.939 --> 44:09.316
could be really important
to all of us.

44:12.277 --> 44:13.362
What do you mean?

44:16.281 --> 44:19.785
I found something
that belonged to the Brave Man

44:21.954 --> 44:26.750
<i>in a place</i>
<i>that he might've been recently.</i>

44:26.834 --> 44:28.585
I don't know
what any of it means yet

44:28.669 --> 44:31.296
or... or if it means
anything at all.

44:31.380 --> 44:32.464
Mom...

44:35.926 --> 44:37.261
is he alive?

44:39.721 --> 44:42.516
I-I don't know, (SNIFFLES) baby.

44:42.599 --> 44:43.684
That's what I'm saying.

44:43.767 --> 44:45.936
<i>I-I-I don't know.</i>

44:47.354 --> 44:49.648
But if you think he's alive,
then you have to go find him.

44:49.731 --> 44:51.441
(SNIFFLES) No.

44:51.525 --> 44:52.901
No. Not now.

44:52.985 --> 44:54.403
<i>You and your brother need me,</i>

44:54.486 --> 44:56.238
and everything going on
in Alexandria...

44:56.321 --> 45:00.784
Mom, you have to go.

45:02.411 --> 45:04.121
You have to.

45:08.333 --> 45:09.585
We're okay.

45:11.712 --> 45:13.422
What if he needs you more?

45:16.508 --> 45:17.926
What if he's trying
to come home, too,

45:18.010 --> 45:20.095
but no one will help?

45:21.180 --> 45:22.681
Ah, God.

45:29.021 --> 45:30.898
(SNIFFLES) If I go...

45:32.816 --> 45:35.944
When you go
and when you find him.

45:36.028 --> 45:39.239
Okay, okay.

45:39.323 --> 45:41.241
When I go...

45:43.577 --> 45:46.747
and find the Brave Man...

45:46.830 --> 45:47.873
(POUNDING)

45:47.956 --> 45:50.626
-JEREMIAH: We're at the coast.
-I have to go.

45:50.709 --> 45:52.836
Listen to Uncle Daryl.

45:52.920 --> 45:53.962
I know.

45:54.046 --> 45:55.839
(CHUCKLES)

45:58.091 --> 45:59.301
Okay.

46:00.719 --> 46:02.763
Okay, baby girl, I'm gonna try.

46:05.057 --> 46:06.433
I'm gonna head north.

46:08.435 --> 46:10.521
And I'll try you
every morning on this walkie

46:10.604 --> 46:11.730
for as long as I can.

46:13.273 --> 46:15.526
I'll take it everywhere.

46:15.609 --> 46:16.860
(SNIFFLES)

46:18.111 --> 46:20.739
I love you and your brother
so much.

46:20.822 --> 46:23.116
Love you, too, Mom.

46:24.284 --> 46:25.369
Go get him.

46:26.995 --> 46:28.372
<i>Shoto, out.</i>

46:32.960 --> 46:35.838
(SIGHS)

46:43.428 --> 46:46.431
(WALKERS GROWLING)

47:26.305 --> 47:28.724
(GRUNTING)

47:37.524 --> 47:39.359
Wait, wait, wait.

47:43.155 --> 47:44.239
Wait.

47:52.998 --> 47:54.708
Can you help us?

47:54.791 --> 47:56.335
They'll leave without us.

47:57.669 --> 47:58.795
Who?

48:03.675 --> 48:05.594
(WALKERS GROWLING)

48:21.276 --> 48:22.361
Please.

48:24.154 --> 48:25.447
They won't wait for us.

48:33.747 --> 48:35.541
CARL:
<i>Should we help her?</i>

48:38.585 --> 48:41.046
<i>RICK: You wanna</i>
<i>tell us your name?</i>

48:41.129 --> 48:42.464
<i>Who are you?</i>

48:47.094 --> 48:49.304
(WALKERS GROWL)

48:59.690 --> 49:00.774
Come on.

49:09.366 --> 49:10.826
(GRUNTS)

49:18.625 --> 49:21.712
(HORSES NEIGHING)

49:40.731 --> 49:42.733
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
